President Cyril Ramaphosa has called for consolidated reports from his Cabinet as the country experiences rapidly rising coronavirus cases. PRETORIA - Spokesperson for the President Khusula Diko has refuted misinformation stating the president will be implementing additional COVID-19 measures on Saturday evening. Coronavirus In SA: Spreading fake news could land you in jail The president is not anticipated to address the nation on Saturday. The National Command Council, in charge of managing the national state of disaster, meets three times a week to discuss the measures needed to address the pandemic. The NCC has a meeting scheduled on Sunday to assess the implementation of the containment measures announced by the president last week and economic relief measures to mitigate the impact of the virus on society. READ: The other virus threat: Surge in COVID-themed cyberattacks The president will update the nation on the outcomes of the meeting at a time that is still to be decided, Diko explained on Twitter. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.